reviews.review_text: Good recording, a little distant This recording is decent and certainly captures a lot of nuance.  It sounds a little distant though to me (FOB, really)?  Jim Wise's recording of this show is preferrable to my ears.  I appreciate Bob putting his recordings out nevertheless.

distance? While this recording may be slightly lacking at the top and the bottom (what do you want from a microphone anyway) I don't get any sense that it is not FOB. Even When the band is playing at lower volume levels the crowd noise is not too objectionable. And the show is smoking. But,hey, get this one and the Jim Wise and make up your own mind.

distance i attribute the amount of crowd sound to the ECM-990, which isn't super-directional. i was definitely at my seat in Section 103, Row P -- I still have the ticket stub. While my memory of being there is hazy after the years, the only available seating chart that I can find shows Section 103 as the left-front section and the soundboard behind ctr-middle section 105.

ECM-990 isnt that a single point mic with 3 mics (1 left, 1 right 1 middle)

sounds like it could be FOB but the mic is pointed at the ceiling leaving the left and right mic to get most of the sound and serve  as the main ones for great seperation
